org.threadly.concurrent

Class CallableDistributor<K,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.concurrent.CallableDistributor<K,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Key for distributing callables and getting results
    R - Type of result that is returned

    public class CallableDistributor<K,R>
extends java.lang.Object

    This abstraction is designed to make submitting Callable tasks with results easier. Tasks are submitted and results for those tasks can be captured when ready using .getNextResult() or .getAllResults(). If multiple callables are submitted with the same key, they are guaranteed to never run in parallel.

      • getNextResult

        public CallableDistributor.Result<R> getNextResult(K key,
                                          boolean resultsExpected)
                                            throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Call to get the next result for a given submission key. This call has the potential to block before a callable has been submitted. This has the risk of blocking forever if a result has already been consumed or the callable is never submitted. But could be useful if the thread that is polling for results is different from the one submitting.
        Parameters:
        key - used when submitted that results will be returned for
        resultsExpected - if callable was guaranteed to be already submitted
        Returns:
        result from execution
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - exception if thread was interrupted while blocking

      • getAllResults

        public java.util.List<CallableDistributor.Result<R>> getAllResults(K key)
                                                            throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Call to return all results currently available for a given submission key. If no results are available, but a callable is running that will produce one, this call will block till results are ready. If there are no callables currently running, and no results waiting, this will throw an IllegalStateException.
        Parameters:
        key - used when submitted that results will be returned for
        Returns:
        a list of all results ready for the given key
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - exception if thread was interrupted while blocking
